HEADWORD: Arteriosclerosis
<hw>Ar*te`ri*o*scle*ro"sis</hw>
<pr>(⟦aum⟧r*t⟦emac⟧`r⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*skl⟦esl⟧*r⟦omac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.; Gr. <?/ artery + <ets>sclerosis</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>a chronic disease characterized by abnormal
thickening and hardening of the walls of the arteries, esp. of the
intima, occurring mostly in old age. Subtypes are distinguished, such as
<er>arteriolosclerosis</er> and <er>atherosclerosis</er>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Ar*te`ri*o*scle*rot"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>arteriosclerotic</ent>⟦br⟧
